                    <citedRange unit="pp">250</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-4" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">a certain old man, poor and a stranger</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">250</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">250</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-5" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            When the<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">old man</persName>came to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2736">the convent</placeName>, the leaders wanted to give him a place of honor. Instead, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">he</persName>chose to sit at the lowest table, refusing even to bless the food. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/food http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/blessing"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">251</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">251</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-6" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Before taking small bites of food or small sips of drink, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the old man</persName>would recite silent prayers. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/food http://syriaca.org/keyword/wine http://syriaca.org/keyword/water http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/blessing"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">252</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">252</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-7" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            After dinner, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the man</persName>began to weep. During evening worship, he appeared to sleep on his rug, crying throughout the night. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/repentance http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/liturgy"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">254</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">254</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-8" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988"/>
                        <occupation ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks">
                            <note>
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">The old man</persName>was a monk for thirty years.
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">255</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">255</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-9" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">The old man</persName>continuously asked the archimandrite of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2736?">the Amida convent</placeName>for a dismissal. Curious, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/76">John</persName>asks the man about his eating, sleeping, and prayer habits. <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">He</persName>eats and prays the way he does out of recognition of human sinfulness. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/sin http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep http://syriaca.org/keyword/food http://syriaca.org/keyword/wine"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">256</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">256</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-10" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            After hearing about<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the old man's</persName>practices, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/76">John</persName>repented of his sins. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/repentance http://syriaca.org/keyword/wine http://syriaca.org/keyword/food http://syriaca.org/keyword/sin http://syriaca.org/keyword/shame http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">257</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">257</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-11" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/76">John</persName>continued to ask <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the old man</persName>for his teaching. In frustruation, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the old man</persName>leaves<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2737">Amida</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">259</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">259</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/809-12" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988"/>
                        <occupation ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorites">
                            <note type="desc">
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1988">the old man</persName>was a solitary.
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/809"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">257</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
